# Keep the proposer image's build context MINIMAL and safe-by-default: exclude everything, then
# re-include EXACTLY the two engine-free files Dockerfile.proposer copies. Consequences:
#   * the engine (edge_search.py / vol_premium.py / cc_backtest.py), the option chains
#     (*_option_dailies*.csv[.gz]), and the answer-key ledger (idea_ledger.jsonl) are never even
#     streamed to the Docker daemon — so a stray `COPY .` could not bake the answer key in;
#   * the build context is tiny (two small .py files), not the whole repo incl. the chain CSVs.
# This is structural defense-in-depth behind the COPY allow-list, not a substitute for it.
*
!proposer_client.py
!read_gate_wire.py
